{
  "texts": [
    "In each of the substitutions performed, using LLM-generated norms did not result in changes of the direction (i.e., sign) for any coefficients across models (see Fig. 4).",
    "However, there were significant changes in the magnitude of coefficients for select predictors, such as age of acquisition and log word frequency (for predicting humangenerated vs. LLM-generated iconicity norms).",
    "The question of viability depends on both theoretical and practical factors.",
    "First, how successfully can GPT-4 reproduce existing human judgments?",
    "Second, how easy is GPT-4 to use in this way, and how would that compare to collecting human judgments at scale?"
  ]
}